<article class="article">
  <h2>What is a recurring deposit?</h2>
  <p>A recurring deposit (RD) is a bank or post-office product where you deposit a fixed amount every month for a chosen tenure — from 6 months to 10 years — and earn a fixed interest rate, credited with quarterly compounding. It is essentially a disciplined FD: the rate certainty of a fixed deposit with the monthly habit of a SIP, which makes it popular for short-term goals like a vacation, gadget, insurance premium or emergency-fund building.</p>

  <h2>How the maturity value is computed</h2>
  <p>Banks treat every instalment as its own small deposit that earns quarterly-compounded interest for the months it remains with the bank:</p>
  <div class="formula">Maturity = Σ P × (1 + r/4)<sup>4 × t<sub>k</sub>/12</sup> &nbsp; for each instalment k</div>
  <p>where t<sub>k</sub> is the number of months instalment k stays deposited. The first instalment earns the most, the last earns interest for just one month — so an RD's overall yield is a little over half the headline rate applied to your total deposits.</p>

  <h2>Worked example</h2>
  <p>₹5,000 a month for 60 months at 7% p.a.: you deposit ₹3,00,000 in total, and maturity comes to about <strong>₹3.59 lakh</strong> — roughly ₹59,000 of interest. Note how this compares with an FD: the same ₹3 lakh invested upfront for 5 years would earn about ₹1.24 lakh, because all the money compounds for the full period.</p>

  <h2>How to use this calculator</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Enter your monthly deposit, the bank's RD rate and tenure in months.</li>
    <li>The chart shows your balance pulling ahead of your cumulative deposits as interest accrues.</li>
    <li>Comparing against mutual funds? Put the same monthly amount into the <a href="/sip-calculator/">SIP calculator</a>.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<script>
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
  function recalc() {
    var p = CM.val('p'), r = CM.val('r') / 100, months = Math.round(CM.val('n'));
    if (p <= 0 || months <= 0) return;

    var fv = 0;
    for (var k = 1; k <= months; k++) {
      var tk = months - k + 1; // months this instalment stays deposited
      fv += p * Math.pow(1 + r / 4, 4 * tk / 12);
    }
    var inv = p * months;
    CM.set('out-fv', CM.inr(fv));
    var w = CM.words(fv);
    CM.set('out-fv-sub', w ? 'about ' + w : '');
    CM.set('out-inv', CM.inr(inv));
    CM.set('out-int', CM.inr(fv - inv));

    var labels = [], valSeries = [], invSeries = [], rows = [];
    for (var mEnd = 12; mEnd <= months || mEnd - 12 < months; mEnd += 12) {
      var upto = Math.min(mEnd, months);
      var v = 0;
      for (var j = 1; j <= upto; j++) v += p * Math.pow(1 + r / 4, 4 * (upto - j + 1) / 12);
      var y = Math.ceil(upto / 12);
      labels.push('Y' + y); valSeries.push(v); invSeries.push(p * upto);
      rows.push([y, CM.inr(p * upto), CM.inr(v - p * upto), CM.inr(v)]);
      if (upto === months) break;
    }
    CM.lineChart('chart-growth', labels, [
      { label: 'Balance', data: valSeries, role: '--s1', fill: true },
      { label: 'Deposited', data: invSeries, role: '--s2' }
    ]);
    CM.table('sched-out', ['Year', 'Deposited', 'Interest', 'Balance'], rows);
  }
  CM.bind(['p', 'r', 'n'], recalc);
});
</script>
